By: Plotinus
---
Our general instinct to seek and learn, our longing to possess ourselves of
whatsoever is lovely in the vision, will set us enquiring into the nature
of the instrument with which we search. Moreover, we shall only be obeying
the ordinance of the God who bade us know ourselves.
